LibreOllama Workspace - Component DetailsThis document provides a thorough description of each UI component within the LibreOllama Workspace design system (v1.1). It elaborates on their purpose, visual characteristics, states, variations, and structural elements.3. Components3.1. ButtonsPurpose: Buttons are used to trigger actions or navigate the user. They are a primary interactive element and should clearly communicate their function.Key Visual Characteristics:Shape: Rounded corners (var(--radius-md): 6px).Typography: Font weight 500 (Medium), font-size: 14px. Text is sentence cased.Layout: inline-flex with centered content. Icons, when present, have a var(--space-2) (8px) gap from the text.Iconography: Lucide icons, typically 16px.States & Variations:Base (.btn): Defines common padding (var(--space-3) var(--space-4)), border-radius, font styles, and transition properties.Primary (.btn-primary):Appearance: Solid background (var(--accent-primary)) with white text.Usage: For the main call to action on a page or within a component.Hover: Darker background (var(--accent-secondary)).Secondary (.btn-secondary):Appearance: Lighter background (var(--bg-tertiary)) with primary text color (var(--text-primary)) and a default border (1px solid var(--border-default)).Usage: For secondary actions or actions that are less prominent than the primary.Hover: Slightly darker background (var(--bg-elevated)).Ghost (.btn-ghost):Appearance: Transparent background, text color var(--text-secondary).Usage: For tertiary actions, often icon-only buttons, or less intrusive actions.Hover: Subtle background (var(--bg-tertiary)), text color var(--text-primary).Padding: var(--space-2) for icon-only versions to maintain a good click target.Sizes (.btn-sm):Appearance: Reduced padding (var(--space-2) var(--space-3)), smaller font size (12px or 13px).Usage: For contexts where space is limited or a less prominent button is needed.Disabled State: Reduced opacity, non-interactive (cursor not-allowed). Backgrounds and text colors are muted.Specific Implementations:Quick Actions Widget Buttons: These btn-primary or btn-secondary buttons justify their content (icon and text) to the start. The icon maintains a var(--space-2) margin to its right.Block Type Toolbar Buttons (Notes): Smaller, using var(--bg-tertiary) background, var(--text-secondary) color, var(--border-default). Icon and short text label. Font size around 12px.Top Bar Action Buttons (.action-btn): Typically icon-only, 36px x 36px, var(--bg-tertiary) background, var(--text-secondary) icon color. Hover changes background to var(--bg-elevated) and icon color to var(--text-primary). The primary "New" button uses var(--accent-primary) background with a white icon.3.2. Input FieldsPurpose: Allow users to enter and edit text or select values. This includes text inputs, search bars, textareas, and select dropdowns.Key Visual Characteristics:Shape: Rounded corners (var(--radius-md): 6px).Background: var(--input-bg) (typically var(--bg-tertiary)).Text Color: var(--text-primary).Placeholder Text Color: var(--input-placeholder) (typically var(--text-tertiary)).Border: 1px solid var(--border-default).Padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4) (12px 16px), but often var(--space-2) var(--space-3) (8px 12px) for a slightly more compact feel as seen in mockups.Font Size: 14px.States & Variations:Focus State: Border color changes to var(--input-focus-ring) (typically var(--accent-primary)), and a subtle box shadow (0 0 0 2px var(--accent-soft)) is applied. Outline is none.Disabled State: Muted background and text, non-interactive.Search Input (.search-input):Icon: A Lucide search icon is absolutely positioned on the left (var(--space-3) from edge), requiring left padding on the input text itself (var(--space-10)).Keyboard Shortcut Hint (.search-kbd): A small visual cue (e.g., "Ctrl+K") absolutely positioned on the right, styled with a muted background and border. Placeholder text reflects the global search scope or context-specific search.Textarea: Similar styling to text input but allows for multi-line text entry. resize: none or vertical is often used.Select Dropdown: Styled to match other input fields, with a dropdown arrow (often a Lucide chevron-down icon) on the right.3.3. NavigationPurpose: Provides users with pathways to different sections and features of the application.Key Visual Characteristics (Main Sidebar - .sidebar):Structure: Fixed width (280px), var(--bg-secondary) background, right border (var(--border-subtle)). Contains header (logo, collapse button), main navigation area (.sidebar-nav), and footer (theme toggle, settings).Sections (.nav-section): Group related navigation items, preceded by a .nav-section-title (uppercase, muted text, 11px).Items (.nav-item):Layout: display: flex, icon aligned with text, var(--space-3) gap.Typography: 14px, font-weight: 500, var(--text-secondary) color.Iconography: Lucide icons, 20px, opacity: 0.8 (default), opacity: 1 on hover/active.Hover State: background: var(--bg-tertiary), color: var(--text-primary).Active State (.active): background: var(--accent-primary), color: var(--text-primary). Icon also adopts primary text color.Badges (.nav-badge): Circular or pill-shaped, var(--accent-primary) background (or semantic colors like var(--error), var(--warning)), white text, 11px.Collapse Button (Conceptual): An icon button (e.g., sidebar-close) in the header to toggle sidebar width.Chat Sidebar (.chat-sidebar):Structure: 320px width, var(--bg-surface) background, right border for separation from main chat.Header (.chat-sidebar-header): "+ New chat" button (primary style). Model selector (.model-selector-wrapper) below it, with a label, dropdown (select element), and status indicator (.model-status).Search/Filter (.chat-search-filter-wrapper): Search input and a filter button (.btn-filter) with a filter icon.Conversation List Sections: "Favorites" (star icon only, no text label), Folders (e.g., "Design Systems" with folder icon, chevron, and item count), "Recent" (clock icon). Section titles are uppercase, muted.List Items (.chat-list-item):Layout: Displays title, optional preview of last message.Metadata: Tags (small pills, var(--bg-tertiary) background), last updated timestamp, participant count with users icon.Hover Actions (.chat-item-actions): Small icon buttons (Pin, Tag, Archive, Delete) appear on hover, typically positioned to the right. These buttons are styled subtly.Active State (.active): background: var(--accent-soft), border-left: 3px solid var(--accent-primary).Pinned State: A pin icon is shown persistently if the item is pinned.Notes Sidebar (.notes-sidebar):Structure: 280px width, var(--bg-secondary) background.Header: "My notebooks" title, "+ New notebook" button (secondary style, full width).Tree Structure (.notebook-tree):Folders (.notebook-folder-title): Display folder icon (open/closed state) and name, chevron for expand/collapse. Active (open) folder background var(--accent-primary).Notes (.note-list-item): Indented under folders. Display file icon and note title. Active note background var(--accent-primary).Project Tabs (.project-tabs - in Project Workspace):Layout: Horizontal list of text labels below the project header.Styling: var(--text-secondary) color. Active tab (.active) has var(--accent-primary) color and a 2px bottom border of var(--accent-primary).View Switcher Tabs (.tasks-views, .calendar-views, .view-tab-group):Layout: Group of button-like elements.Styling: Inactive tabs use var(--bg-tertiary) background, var(--text-primary) color, var(--border-default). Active tab (.active) uses var(--accent-primary) background and white text.3.4. Cards & WidgetsPurpose: Modular containers for displaying distinct pieces of information or functionality, primarily on the Dashboard but also within other views (e.g., Project Overview).Key Visual Characteristics (.widget, .card):Shape: Rounded corners (var(--radius-lg): 8px or 12px).Background: var(--bg-surface).Border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle).Padding: var(--space-6) (24px).Shadow: Subtle var(--shadow-md) on hover for widgets.Structure (Widgets):Drag Handle (.widget-drag-handle): A subtle grip icon (e.g., grip-vertical), often appearing on hover for customizable widgets, positioned top-right.Header (.widget-header):Contains widget title (.widget-title: 18px, font-weight: 600).Optional actions (.widget-actions): Group of small, icon-only ghost buttons (e.g., more options, settings).Content Area: Varies based on widget type (e.g., progress bars, lists, charts).Variations:Project Progress Widget: Displays title, percentage, progress bar (.progress-bar with .progress-fill), and list of milestones (.milestone-list with status dots).Events Widget: Lists events (.event-item) with time (.event-time), title (.event-title), and metadata/indicator dot (.event-indicator).Agent Status Widget: Lists AI agents (.ai-agent-item) with status dot (.agent-status-dot), name, model, and usage.Quick Actions Widget: Grid (.quick-actions-grid) of primary/secondary buttons with icons and text.3.5. Modals & OverlaysPurpose: To present focused information or actions without navigating away from the current context.Overlay Backdrop (.overlay):Appearance: Semi-transparent dark background (var(--bg-overlay)), backdrop-filter: blur(8px). Covers the entire viewport.Behavior: Typically appears with a modal or palette centered or positioned within it.Command Palette (.command-palette):Appearance: Max-width 640px, var(--bg-surface) background, var(--radius-xl) border radius, var(--shadow-xl). Centered towards the top of the viewport.Structure: Header with input field (.command-palette-input), scrollable results area (.command-palette-results) with sections (.command-palette-section-title) and items (.command-palette-item). Items show icon, title, description, and optional keyboard shortcut (.command-palette-item-kbd).Interaction: Input field is auto-focused. Items are selectable via keyboard/mouse.Settings Modal (.settings-modal):Appearance: Max-width 800px, var(--bg-surface) background, var(--radius-xl) border radius, var(--shadow-xl). Centered in viewport.Structure: Two-column layout:Left: Settings navigation sidebar (.settings-sidebar) with nav-item styling.Right: Settings content area (.settings-content) with sections (.settings-section-title) and individual settings (.settings-item). Settings items often include a title, description, and a control (e.g., toggle switch, select dropdown).Notification Panel (.notification-panel):Appearance: Fixed position (typically top-right, below top bar), width 360px, var(--bg-surface) background, var(--radius-lg), var(--shadow-xl).Structure: Header with title and close button. Scrollable list (.notification-list) of notification items (.notification-item), each with an icon, title, description, and timestamp.Widget Gallery (.panel-sidebar as used for Widget Gallery):Appearance: Slides in from the right, width 400px, var(--bg-surface) background, var(--shadow-xl).Structure: Header with title and close button. Scrollable content area with sections and a grid (.widget-gallery-grid) of available widgets (.widget-gallery-item), each showing an icon and title.3.6. Chat Elements (Main Chat Area)Header (.chat-header):Left Side (.chat-header-left):Breadcrumb (.chat-breadcrumb-main): Shows folder context if applicable (e.g., "Folder Name >").Current Chat Title (.chat-title): Prominent, 16px, font-weight: 600.Right Side (.chat-header-controls):Model Selector (.model-selector-main-header): Compact dropdown (select) showing current AI model, with status indicator (dot + "Ready").Chat Actions (.chat-actions): Group of ghost buttons (e.g., "Add to project," "Export").Message Bubbles (.message):Layout: Max-width 85% of chat area. User messages (.user) aligned right, AI messages (.ai) aligned left. Includes avatar and content wrapper.Avatars (.message-avatar): 32px, rounded (var(--radius-sm)), distinct styles for user (accent background) and AI (elevated surface background with border). Displays initials or AI logo.Sender Name (.message-sender): Small text (12px, var(--text-tertiary)) above the message content.Content (.message-content):User: var(--accent-primary) background, white text, var(--radius-lg).AI: var(--bg-surface) background, var(--border-default), var(--radius-lg).Typography: 14px body text, line-height: 1.6.Code Blocks: Nested within message content. var(--bg-tertiary) background (or rgba(255,255,255,0.1) for user messages), monospace font, scrollable if needed. Includes a header with language hint and a prominent "Copy" button (with icon and text).Attachments (.message-attachments):PDF Preview (.attachment-preview-pdf): Thumbnail-like box with file-type icon, filename, and a "Preview" button.Generic File (.attachment-preview-generic): Simpler display with file icon and filename.Input Area (.chat-input-area):Textarea (.chat-input): min-height: 48px, var(--bg-elevated) background, placeholder "Ask about design, code, or anything else... (Ctrl+Enter to send)".Send Button (.chat-send-btn): Accent color, send icon, positioned inside the textarea on the right.Controls (.chat-input-controls):Left: Attachment buttons (.attachment-btn for files, images).Right: Context indicator (.context-indicator e.g., "1 file • 256 tokens"), "Clear context" button.3.7. Note Editor BlocksEditor Header (.notes-editor-header):Note Title (.note-title-display): 26px, font-weight: 600.Actions (.note-actions): Row of subtle ghost icon buttons (Star, Share, History, More).Block Type Toolbar (.block-type-toolbar):Position: Directly below the editor header, above the first content block.Appearance: Row of small buttons (.block-type-btn), each with an icon and short text label (e.g., "Text", "H1", "List", "Code", "Sketch"). Styled with var(--bg-tertiary) and var(--border-default).Content Area (.notes-editor-content): Max-width 768px for readability, centered.Individual Blocks (.editor-block):Structure: Each block is a distinct container with margin-bottom: var(--space-4) for separation.Hover Controls (.block-menu - conceptual for static): Placeholder for drag handle and add block button, appearing to the left on hover.Placeholder/Initial Block (.block-content.placeholder-text): Text "Type '/' for commands, or just start writing..." with subtle inline formatting hint icons (Bold, Italic, Underline).Paragraph (.block-content or <p>): Standard text 16px, line-height: 1.7.Headings (.block-content.heading1, .heading2):H1: 30px, font-weight: 600, border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-tertiary).H2: 24px, font-weight: 600.Lists (ol, ul): Standard HTML list styling, indented. Action items use a -  prefix style.Checklist (.block-content.checklist .task-item): Custom styled checkboxes (input[type="checkbox"]) and labels. Completed items are struck through and muted.Code Block (.block-content.code-block): var(--bg-secondary) background, monospace font, "Copy" button.Image Placeholder (.block-content.image-placeholder): Dashed border, centered icon and text.Table Block (.block-content.table-block table): Standard HTML table with borders on th and td. th has a var(--bg-surface) background.Sketch Placeholder (.sketch-block): Dashed border, icon (image-plus), placeholder text.Wiki-Link (.wiki-link): var(--accent-primary) color, dotted var(--accent-primary) underline.Floating Action Button (.fab):Appearance: Circular, 48px x 48px, var(--bg-elevated) background, var(--text-secondary) icon color, var(--border-default).Position: Bottom-right of the notes editor area. Contains a plus icon.3.8. Calendar ElementsHeader (.calendar-header):Navigation (.calendar-nav): Previous/Next month buttons (icon-only), current month/year title (.calendar-title), "Today" button.View Switcher (.calendar-views .calendar-view-btn): Tabs for "Month", "Week", "Day". Active tab uses var(--accent-primary) background.Grid (.calendar-grid):Header Cells (.calendar-header-cell): Display day names (Sun, Mon, etc.).Day Cells (.calendar-day): min-height, padding..other-month: Muted appearance..today .calendar-day-number: Accent background, white text.Day Number (.calendar-day-number): Prominently displayed.Event Items (.calendar-event):Appearance: Rounded corners, colored background based on event type (e.g., default var(--accent-secondary), meeting var(--success), task var(--warning)). White text.Layout: Displays event title, truncated if too long.Time-Blocking Panel (.time-blocking-panel):Appearance: Separate sidebar-like panel (typically on the right), 280px width, var(--bg-surface) background.Structure: Header (.time-blocking-title), scrollable content area with sections for tasks (.task-section-title, .task-item draggable placeholders).3.9. Kanban Board (Tasks Module)Header (.tasks-header):Page Title (.tasks-title).Controls (.tasks-controls): View switcher tabs (Kanban/List), "+ New task" button (primary).Board (.kanban-board-wrapper):Layout: Horizontal scroll using display: flex.Columns (.kanban-column):Appearance: 320px width, var(--bg-surface) background, var(--radius-lg).Header (.kanban-column-header): Column title (e.g., "To Do" with icon), task count (.kanban-column-count), "more options" icon button.Content (.kanban-column-content): Scrollable area for task cards.Add Task Button (.add-task-btn): Dashed button at the bottom of the content area.Task Cards (.kanban-task):Appearance: var(--bg-elevated) background, var(--radius-md), var(--border-default).Structure:Header (.kanban-task-header): Task title (.kanban-task-title), optional task ID (.kanban-task-id).Description (.kanban-task-description): Optional, truncated.Footer (.kanban-task-footer):Metadata (.kanban-task-meta): Priority indicator (.kanban-task-priority - styled with high/medium/low classes using semantic colors), due date (.kanban-task-due - styled if overdue).Assignee Avatar (.kanban-task-assignee): Circular, displays initials or image.List View (.task-list-view):Appearance: Standard table (.task-list-table) with th and td.Columns: Checkbox, Title, Status, Priority (using .priority-dot), Due Date, Assignee (using .assignee-avatar-sm), Project, Actions (more options icon).3.10. Agent Cards (Agents Module)Card (.agent-card):Appearance: var(--bg-surface) background, var(--radius-lg), var(--border-subtle).Layout: display: flex, flex-direction: column.Structure:Header (.agent-card-header):Icon Wrapper (.agent-icon-wrapper): Styled container for a Lucide icon representing the agent type.Agent Info (.agent-info): Name (.agent-name - 16px, font-weight: 600), Model (.agent-model - 12px, var(--text-tertiary)).Status Dot (.agent-status-dot): online (var(--success)) or offline (var(--text-muted)).Description (.agent-description): 14px, var(--text-secondary).Capabilities (.agent-capabilities):Title (.capabilities-title).List (.capabilities-list) of tags (.capability-tag - var(--bg-tertiary) background, var(--text-secondary) text).Actions (.agent-actions): "Configure" button (secondary), "Delete" button (ghost, positioned right).Create Agent Card (Placeholder): Visually distinct (e.g., dashed border, centered "+" icon and text) to invite user action.This detailed breakdown should provide a solid reference for implementing each component of the LibreOllama Workspace with consistency and high quality.